txt.en: 'And I am no rat!'
'Until the moment the whips of Mordor are lashed upon your back, you will be blind to the fate you have chosen for our people.'
'I expected more than this lot... where have they all gone?'
'I do not come for vengeance. I shall save Umbar from scum like Balakhôr!'
Instance: Sons of the Usurper
'The four of us have come only for you, Azgarzôr.'
'I will hang your bodies from the walls of Pelargir!'
'You shall join your brother soon, fools!'
'I hear more coming, brother. We have been discovered!'
'Swiftly now, free their steeds and frighten them! Let us throw these men into disarray!'
'It is you who shall bring Umbar to ruin, traitor!'
'Balakhôr will slay you all!'
'Lead on, brother!'
'Lay down your weapons now and we might slay you quickly.'
'Fine. You have forsaken our Way, traitor, and you will suffer.'
'That must be his tent ahead! Let us go!'
'I have burned the ships along the river's edge, but I do not promise that will keep them busy much longer. So let us finish this, eh?'
'Well, come on!'
'So the brothers of Linhir come to avenge their murderous kin?'
'Tell me something, warrior. Do the depths of the Gilrain treat him well?'
'I was unaware that I had two Gondorian warriors in my service...'
'...unless, of course, the rat hiding between you had some need of your aid.'
'And what of you? Why aid the men of Gondor?'
'I give you the lead, Corsair. Let us move!'
'So be it...'
'If you would fight together, then you shall die together!'
'On your feet, fools! They are here!'
'And you as well. You have helped me to free my people from the Heirs... I shall not forget this, my friends. Hah, perhaps you folk are not so bad after all!'
'Brother! Look ahead, we have been spotted!'
'That's far enough!'
'Herion, [placeholder]... we move now!'
'Hey! Be careful where you point your blade, Swan-man!'
'I suppose this is where we part ways... you go back to your adventures, [placeholder], and I... I shall take to the sea.'
'Let us see how they handle that! Onwards!'
'Up the hill, swiftly now! We must press on before more of them discover what has happened.'
'[placeholder], do you know this man? He makes no move to attack us.'
'Rest well, Garvir, for you are avenged!'
'Fare well, Jajax. Indeed, you are a strange man, but I shall not forget what you have done for my family.'
'Enough words! None will sully Garvir's name in my presence!'
'Cut them down!'
'If you are friends of [placeholder], you need not worry yourselves, Swan-men!'
